          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-9747 tests: compare Lustre/ZFS to local ext4 POSIX",
        "message": "LU-9747 tests: compare Lustre/ZFS to local ext4 POSIX\n\nThe Lustre test script that checks POSIX compliance runs\ntesting twice; once on a local file system and then with\nLustre.  These results are compared to check Lustre’s POSIX\ncompliance.\n\nTest if local ext4 POSIX results are the same as Lustre/ZFS.\nIf ext4 and Lustre/ZFS are not similarly POSIX compliant,\nthen we need to try to install ZFS on the client and run the\nfirst pass of POSIX testing on the local ZFS file system.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial fstype=zfs testlist=posix\nTest-Parameters: fstype=zfs mdscount=2 mdtcount=4 testlist=posix\nSigned-off-by: James Nunez <jnunez@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I44dc8da39027e43745a28ad20605986972fda422\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
